# Corpus scope for the graphify knowledge graph (gitignore syntax).
# NOTE: when this file exists graphify stops falling back to .gitignore, so
# any .gitignore rule that matters for extraction must be repeated here
# (node_modules, .next, .git, graphify-out are built-in skips already).

# Mirrored from .gitignore — local artifacts and secrets, never corpus
/test-results
/playwright-report
/blob-report
.env*
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
supabase/dev/link_test_users.sql
supabase/dev/link_super_admin.sql

# Tooling infrastructure, not the codebase the graph should describe
.husky/
.claude/
.agents/
skills-lock.json

# Documentation: the graph describes the code architecture; prose docs and
# their dense cross-links drown the code signal (root-anchored so the
# graphify-out/memory/ loop keeps re-ingesting saved answers).
/docs/
/*.md
/.github/

# Shell scripts: graphify's bash extractor embeds the absolute checkout path
# in file/entry node IDs, which breaks graph reproducibility across machines.
# Remove this once fixed upstream (https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify).
*.sh
